6000|$|Lastly I may {{add that}} many {{instances}} {{have been recorded}} of flowers, not generally considered as <b>peloric,</b> in which certain organs are abnormally augmented in number. As an increase of parts cannot be looked at as an arrest of development, nor as due to the redevelopment of rudiments, for no rudiments are present, and as these additional parts bring the plant into closer relationship with its natural allies, they ought probably {{to be viewed as}} reversions to a primordial condition.] ...|$|E
