50|$|It is an epiphytic orchid with grouped pseudobulbs {{growing to}} 2-5 cm in height. The terminal, ovate-elliptic leaves are 10-12 mm long and 5-10 mm wide. The <b>peloric</b> flowers are pale cream and borne on terminal, 2- or 3-flowered inflorescences.|$|E
50|$|Though perennial, {{the species}} is often {{cultivated}} as a biennial or annual plant, particularly in colder areas where it may not survive the winter. Numerous cultivars are available, including plants with lavender, orange, pink, yellow, or white flowers, and also plants with <b>peloric</b> flowers, where the normal flowering spike is topped with a single large, symmetrical flower.|$|E
